The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 First Epsom for Dwyer 

 Epsom: Sir Percy, a 6-1 chance ridden by Martin Dwyer, snatched a short head victory from 66-1 outsider Dragon Dancer in the $2.3 million Epsom Derby on Saturday.

 In one of the closest finishes to the premier classic for years, pace-making Dylan Thomas, a 25-1 chance in the field of 18, finished third just a head behind the runner-up.

 It was a first Derby victory for jockey Dwyer and trainer Marcus Tregoning. Second favourite Horatio Nelson, the mount of Kieren, Fallon, broke down in the straight.The winners purse was $1.37 million. (REUTERS)




